investigation.title: Molecular Transducers of Human Skeletal Muscle Remodeling under Different Loading States
investigation.description: The annotation of the Affymetrix HTA 2.0 array was updated to optimise the detection of RNA in human skeletal muscle biopsy samples by removing invalid and low signal-high-variance probes (as for CDF GPL24047). The probes were then summarized into groups (probe-sets) reflecting either an ensembl full transcript identifier (FL-ENST, GPL24047) or just the probes targeting the 3' UTR or the 5' UTR of that particular ENST.

project.funding: This work was funded by a grant to S.M.P. from the National Science and Engineering Research Council (NSERC) of Canada (RGPIN-2020). Part of the informatics work was supported by Medical Research Council UK G1100015 (to J.A.T.) and by the EU FP7 program (277936). Additional informatics analysis costs were supported by J.A.T.
